node.text: Here ya go, all 13 attempts of the kong gainer pre! I almost called it off twice because of the 3rd and then the 7th attempt when I thought I was gonna die. 😂 So glad I was persistent! I was gonna upload a full YouTube video showing the whole process but the BTS footage kinda spoils another trick I’m working on so you’ll have to wait for it. 👌 Thank you all for the kind words and hype, I can’t believe it has over half a million views now! 2022 is gonna be my best year yet. ❤️ #konggainerpre #canthurtmecookiejar #freerunning #parkour #calenchan

node.text: Did my first cork pres outside today, wanted to swing through but the wall was so slippery I literally couldn't block harder without slipping which means I basically got zero height. Even tried brushing the dust off and pouring coke on it and didn't make it better. 😪 Need to find a better spot to try it again. 🤙 #freerunning #tricking #cork #calenchan #baneblade

node.text: Just dropped this video announcement of @banebladejam2021 on my YouTube channel! September 23rd-25th in Utah County we are gonna throw down!! The competition is gonna be dope and have custom medals and cash prizes, and the jam is free and we gonna have a freaking barbecue! I'm selling new awesome shirts at the event too and launching my new brand, Baneblade! If you are competing or going to the open gym sesh on the 24th, REGISTER NOW by clicking the link in my bio because the more people we know are competing, the bigger we can make the prizes and the next year's competition!! SEE YA THERE HOMIES!!!!! 🔥 #banebladejam2021 #lowesolympics @lowesairsports

node.text: This is how I hurt my shoulder a week ago. This was like my 8th try on a tough to flow line that I guess I was too tired for. I jinxed it that day by saying "I'm glad I don't have to deal with shoulder injuries". It's improved a lot since then but I still can't do any flips without severe pain except for a webster side while holding my arm. SO frustrating but at least I get to work on preparing for @banebladejam2021 and my new clothing brand! 💪 #fail #freerunning #ouch

node.text: Trying new things, relearning old things. Tdr in back out is so freaking hard, I'll venmo 5 bucks to someone who can land it. (EDIT: My wife reminded me that we don't have money and told me to take that off my post.) 😂 Also improved my cast gainer tech but still a huge mental battle and haven't gotten the nerve to take it outside of foampit in over a year. Idk why it's so scary now. 🤷‍♂️ #freerunning #tricking #calenchan

node.text: Cork-in is easier than trip cork, change my mind. 🤷‍♂️😅 Worked on twisting today and regaining ariel-awareness. It's really hard to focus on tech in the air when you're struggling to trust your body on the landing, and that made cork-in so hard to commit to again, even with lots of pads. Glad I overcame the fear and did my first ones since my ankle injury a year ago! 😁 #freerunning #calenchan #corkinbackout #tricking #redbull

node.text: What a day. I looked at this spot 6 years ago and imagined doing kong gainer pre here, never knew I’d ever actually achieve it. Today I wanted to try something a bit more ambitious than this but the progressions were not promising so I called it off. I could’ve gone home and gave up but decided I needed to do at least something new today that I’d be proud of. ❤️ I am pleased to say that none of my kong gainer pre attempts missed the wall, and I was able to consistently do them 13 times in a row ending with this extremely satisfying stick. This is the hardest I have pushed my mental game in almost 4 years, and a reminder for me that with God’s help you can do almost anything you set your mind to. Huge thank you to the friends that came out today to support me in the freezing weather! 🙏🙏 🎥: @setherson_wright #freerunning #konggainerpre #calenchan

node.text: KONG DOUBLE GAINER TO GRASS!!! 🙌 It’s been a month and a half and I’m finally deciding to post it because of @redbull AOM submissions, which I just uploaded to YouTube! I’ve dreamed of this trick since 2016 when I did it onto pads in a gym, but I wanted to take it to sand first which was something I didn’t have where I lived. A couple months ago I found the perfect spot at Venice Pier and stomped it on sand within less than 30 minutes and turned out to be way easier than the ones I did in the gym years ago. I decided not to post it because I wanted to take it to grass. I knew the impact would require a roll so I prepared the best I could. When the day finally came I ended up doing it twice, first time I under-rotated and had a very sloppy roll but I wasn’t harmed. The second time (this one) I landed and rolled way cleaner but the sheer impact ended up bruising my bone and spraining my foot taking me out for over a month. Nevertheless I ran out of it and I’m so satisfied with how the clip turned out. This means so much to me because of how mental this challenge was. I never got close to attempting it before because every time I’d visualize it, I could only see myself landing on my head and LITERALLY dying. Trying to really go hard this year and see how far I can go, always I must credit Heavenly Father for guiding me and blessing me in my journey. Thank you all for your support, big things coming this year! ❤️ #redbull #calenchan #parkour #flip #firstintheworld #dub #stuntman #insane #motivation #xgamesmode #freerunning @ygtfreerunning
